  "calculator_allowed": true,
  "total_points": 9,
  "stimulus": "At an intersection in Thomasville, Oregon, cars turn left at the rate $L(t) = 60\\sqrt{t}\\sin^2\\!\\left(\\tfrac{t}{3}\\right)$ cars per hour over the time interval $0 \\le t \\le 18$ hours.",
  "stimulus_image": null,
  "documents": null,
  "parts": [
    {
      "letter": "a",
      "prompt": "To the nearest whole number, find the total number of cars turning left at the intersection over the time interval $0 \\le t \\le 18$ hours.",
      "point_value": 2,
      "scoring_notes": null,
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "a1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct integral setup",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$\\int_0^{18} L(t)\\, dt$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\int_0^{18} L(t)\\, dt$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct answer (nearest whole number)",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct numerical answer"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\approx 1658$ cars"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "Traffic engineers will consider turn restrictions when $L(t) \\ge 150$ cars per hour. Find all values of $t$ for which $L(t) \\ge 150$ and compute the average value of $L$ over this time interval. Indicate units of measure.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": null,
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "b1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct $t$-interval when $L(t) \\ge 150$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$L(t) = 150$ at $t \\approx 12.428$ and $t \\approx 16.122$",
                "Interval $[12.428, 16.122]$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct average value integral",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$\\frac{1}{S-R}\\int_R^S L(t)\\, dt$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\frac{1}{16.122 - 12.428}\\int_{12.428}^{16.122} L(t)\\, dt$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct average with units",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct numerical answer",
                "Units of cars per hour"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\approx 199.426$ cars per hour"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "c",
      "prompt": "Traffic engineers will install a signal if there is any two-hour time interval during which the product of the total number of cars turning left and the total number of oncoming cars traveling straight through the intersection is greater than 200,000. In every two-hour time interval, 500 oncoming cars travel straight through the intersection. Does this intersection require a traffic signal? Explain the reasoning that leads to your conclusion.",
      "point_value": 4,
      "scoring_notes": null,
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "c1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Considers correct threshold (400 cars in 2-hour window)",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Product $> 200{,}000$ requires $> 400$ cars turning left in 2-hour window"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "c2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Valid 2-hour interval identified",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Any 2-hour subinterval $[h, h+2]$ contained in $[13, 15.3]$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "c3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Computes integral over identified interval",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$\\int_{13}^{15} L(t)\\, dt > 400$"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$\\int_{13}^{15} L(t)\\, dt \\approx 431.9 > 400$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "c4",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct answer and explanation",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Yes, a signal is required",
                "Product exceeds 200,000"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
